text=I hate making up names. It's slow, time consuming and they don't tend to sound any good.%0a%0aAs a bonus extra, if you use something you're not satisfied with as a placeholder it tends to stick%0awith the character/place for evermore.%0a%0aTo get fairly consistent and real sounding names, I've taken the decision that the names in Pamant on %0aRomanian - or at least on [[http://translate.google.com/translate_t?sl=en&tl=ro | Google Translate]]'s best%0aguess at Romanian. Notice I said based on: I'll be tweaking things to make them sound better to the English %0aspeaking ear, merging words to create names and generally using it for inspiration.%0a%0aBut at least it will free up the actual writing process, rather than spending all of my limited writing time %0atrying and discarding names.%0a%0aAs well as using Google Translate, it means I can also just use lists of ([[http://www.20000-names.com/male_romanian_names.htm | male]] and [[http://www.20000-names.com/female_romanian_names.htm | female]]) real %0aRomanian names and still have them fit in style with the setting.%0a%0aSo, why Pamant? Because it's earth in Romanian...
